 Years, 1800\u20131815|publisher=Greenwood Press|isbn=978-0-313-30997-7 |page=119 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=0NBnAAAAMAAJ}}\n* {{Citation |last=Longford |first=Elizabeth |authorlink=Elizabeth Longford |year=1971 |title=Wellington the Years of the Sword |publisher=London: Panther| isbn=978-0-586-03548-1}}\n* {{Citation |last=Low |first=E. Bruce |year=1911 |chapter=The Waterloo Papers |editor-last=MacBride |editor-first= M. |title=With Napoleon at Waterloo |location=London |chapter-url=https://archive.org/details/withnapoleonatwa00macbuoft}}\n* {{Citation |last=Lozier |first=J.F. |date=18 June 2010 |url=http://www.napoleon-series.org/faq/c_horses.html |title=What was the name of Napoleon's horse? |publisher= The Napoleon Series |accessdate=29 March 2009}}\n* {{Citation |last=Mantle |first=Robert |date=December 2000 |title=Prussian Reserve Infantry 1813\u20131815: Part II: Organisation |publisher=Napoleonic Association |url=http://www.napoleon-series.org/military/organization/c_resinf2.html|accessdate=}}.{{better source|date=June 2013}}\n* {{Citation |last=Marcelis |first=David |date=10 June 2015 |url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/when-napoleon-met-his-waterloo-he-was-out-of-town-1433894903 |title=When Napoleon Met His Waterloo, He Was Out of Town |newspaper=Wall Street Journal}}\n* {{Citation |last=Mercer |first=A.C. |year=1870a |title=Journal of the Waterloo Campaign: Kept Throughout the Campaign of 1815 |volume=1 |location=Edinburgh and London |publisher=W. Blackwood |url=https://archive.org/details/journalofwaterlo01mercuoft}}\n* {{Citation |last=Mercer |first=A.C. |year=1870b |chapter=Waterloo, 18 June 1815: The Royal Horse Artillery Repulse Enemy Cavalry, late afternoon |title=Journal of the Waterloo Campaign: Kept Throughout the Campaign of 1815 |volume=2 |chapter-url=https://archive.org/details/journalofwaterlo02mercuoft}}\n* {{citation |author-last=Mercer |author-first=A.C. |author-link=Cavali\u00e9 Mercer |year=1891 |chapter=No 89:Royal Artillery |