e.tiscali.nl/erwinmuilwijk/index.htm Contribution of the Netherlands Mobile Army during the 1815 campaign]. Gives full account of the Dutch troops that fought at [[Battle of Quatre Bras|Quatre-Bras]], based on many unknown primary sources.-->\n* de Wit, Pierre. [http://www.waterloo-campaign.nl/ The campaign of 1815: a study]. Study of the campaign of 1815, based on sources from all participating armies.\n* {{Citation|title=The Cowards at Waterloo|url=http://www.napolun.com/mirror/napoleonistyka.atspace.com/Waterloo_Cowards.html|accessdate=23 March 2013|ref=none}} based on {{citation |last=Dellevoet|first=A. |title=Cowards at Waterloo?: A Re-Examination of Bijlandt's Dutch-Belgian Brigade in the Campaign of 1815 |year=2001|publisher=Stackpole books |ref=none}}\n\n===Books===\n* {{Citation| last=Bonaparte| first=Napoleon |year=1995 |editor1-last=Chandler |editor1-first=David G. | editor2-last=Cairnes |editor2-first=William E. |title=The Military Maxims of Napoleon|publisher=Da Capo Press |isbn=978-0-306-80618-6|ref=none}}\n* {{Citation |last=Chandler |first=David G. |year=1973 |title=Campaigns of Napoleon |publisher=New York: Scribner |isbn=978-0-02-523660-8 |ref=none |url=https://archive.org/details/campaignsofnapol00chan }}\n* {{Citation |last=Chilcott | first=Christopher | year=2015 |title=The Royal Waggon Train: Maintaining the British Army 1803\u20131833 | publisher=RLC Association Trust Fund |ref=none}}\n* {{Citation |last1=[[Carl von Clausewitz|Clausewitz]] |first1=Carl von |last2=Wellesley |first2=Arthur |editor=Christopher Bassford |editor2=Daniel Moran |editor3=Gregory Pedlow |year=2010| url=http://www.clausewitz.com/readings/1815/index.htm |title=On Waterloo: Clausewitz, Wellington, and the Campaign of 1815 | publisher=Clausewitz.com |isbn=978-1-4537-0150-8|ref=none}} This on-line text contains Clausewitz's 58-chapter study of the ''Campaign of 1815'' and Wellington's lengthy 1842 essay written in response to Clausewitz, as well as supporting documents and 